trans-unit.source: Represents a simplified configuration element used for updating elements in the configuration.
This class cannot be inherited.
Represents a configuration element within a configuration file.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> class based on supplied parameters.
The name of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> object.
A <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingsSerializeAs"></xref> object.
This object is an enumeration used as the serialization scheme to store configuration settings.
Compares the current <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> instance to the specified object.
The object to compare with.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> instance is equal to the specified object; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets a unique value representing the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> current instance.
A unique value representing the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> current instance.
Gets or sets the name of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> object.
The name of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> object.

The <xref:System.Configuration.SettingsSerializeAs> object is an enumeration used as the serialization scheme to store configuration settings.
A <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingsSerializeAs"></xref> object.

A <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingValueElement"></xref> object containing the value of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SettingElement"></xref> object.
